<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause xmlns:xt="urn:xpressauthor:trackchanges" id="_d14cf7be-3a32-41fe-8548-37881e97f7f4" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 2"/><facet building="Class 3"/><facet building="Class 4"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7a"/><facet building="Class 7b"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9a"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 9c"/><facet building="Class 10b"/><facet building="Class 10c"/></meta><sptc>H3P2</sptc><title id="_a2faa813-f5b6-4ec2-a33f-1b05736af95e">Automatic warning for occupants</title><archive-num>2019: P2.3.2</archive-num><subclause id="_c3366ba3-25e0-442c-a4aa-511fb8275d4e" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_e67af101-5dcd-41a5-af40-8af0a0d765ab">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>In a Class 1 building, occupants must be provided with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1199_0.7.0.xml#_ac370c9b-7389-4daa-ac5b-338e11dc43e7" id="_ce05eaac-364e-4a23-bde2-1db8ce7e5798" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">automatic</xref> warning on the detection of smoke with an <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/4931_0.3.0.xml#_2e774679-ab79-4817-b344-0ce56a475882" id="_6213da70-c219-44af-8a5f-c81603275991" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">efficacy</xref> greater than 0.95 and a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/4932_0.3.0.xml#_02cf4ab9-bcd0-4114-b257-312bdd83d376" id="_459bf5d5-66f2-4dcd-b371-83748e28b684" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">reliability</xref> greater than 0.95, so that they may evacuate in the event of a fire to a place of safety appropriate to the—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_f6d469e6-27bf-4bb4-9998-94428e11b815">function and use of the building; and</li><li id="_9da2ed5b-56b5-41a9-9317-53ec2894d377">occupant characteristics; and</li><li id="_d542e717-2e86-415a-b79c-ed5d32e97fdf"><xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1286_2.8.0.xml#_c6f00a2d-3f92-463d-8e6f-1f215ea421d5" id="_65ebc6c0-5454-4cb2-99ec-565e1a387a80" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">fire load</xref> and combustion characteristics; and</li><li id="_3c7f74ad-07cc-447d-947b-4a78788065ea">potential <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1282_0.4.0.xml#_7b10d376-72de-4ed5-9262-35f2d1a39ecc" id="_dee57cde-ed03-496b-ba93-b63fd3067fd4" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">fire intensity</xref>; and </li><li id="_33cc865a-e87f-4183-b6aa-25df9992c529"><xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1279_0.4.0.xml#_7babb9ed-37aa-4441-b7da-93711bfa5283" id="_abf3a249-d599-4a80-88ff-bc5b0141842a" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">fire hazard</xref>.</li></ol></subclause></clause>